  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Assistance to Stranded and Vulnerable Migrants in Southern Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of intervention is to reduce the suffering of vulnerable migrants affected by COVID-19 in South Africa through the provision of life-saving humanitarian assistance. To achieve this objective, the project, in coordination with the respective Civil Society Organizations (CSOs), as well as Embassies and High Commissions will provide food assistance through the provision of food vouchers to 3,550 migrants through a one-off voucher transfer to enable migrants to purchase essential food items. The voucher will allow migrants to shop at their store of choice, and thus to contribute towards the recovery of smaller businesses in host communities during COVID-19.</narrative>
  </description>
